      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHANGE TACT NZ (3) made a winning return from Queensland when she led from a wider barrier and dug deep to get home last week, taking her record at this circuit and distance to two from three. Tackles the boys this time but has the speed to take advantage of the lower draw. HAPPY TOO YA (2) has trialled well since he worked and faded as favourite last start. Put together a string of wins earlier in the campaign, one of them coming here when he led from this barrier so expect him to be prominent. MONTEFIORE NZ (4) draws lower than when midfield here on Tuesday and had missed narrowly from this barrier here prior. Could be working towards a win as could MICK DANGER (1) who placed two back before racing parked when beaten 3.2m last time. Building nicely and gets the ace draw. Would prefer a lower barrier for PETES CRUNCH TIME (8) but his best form would measure up.",
